22-12 : How sweet is it? (Ode to our simple, habit filled life)
	Some say routine is a silent killer for couple. Some say, you should try to avoid doing the same things everyday.
	If we take their point of view, they might imagine that a life such as ours is too simple. Maybe they imagine that there is no thrill, that we might like what they like to label as "new experiences". "On their side", it is clear that they are seaking something we're not after. 
	And I think there lies the key to the mystery of how sweet our life is. 
	For whatever they might feel when they are in a party, with random strangers, having drugs, alcohol or hooking up with std filled weirdos, simply pales in comparison to what I feel when I see your smile when I wake you up with kisses. 
	They might feel excitment, fun, maybe some tingling in their stomachs but have they ever felt this rush, this sensation starting from your feet all the way to your neck. Remember when we would drive and suddenly we feel our organs when the road is in this specific curve? The feeling resembles this one, at least physically. Emotionally, it translates to this urge, this sudden duty. This smile must stay on. No matter what. As if an addict had to protect the precious stash that will keep providing him with that sensation.
	Therefore, these people might be seaking that tingling, that fun, to compensate for what we already have - the real thing. Much like foreigners going to the grocery store and buying "Bonne Maman" confiture when we already know what Papy's tastes like. They can keep running after what they think they need. But we know better.
